[[File:Tizi'n'Toubkal.jpg|thumb|[[Toubkal]], at {{convert|4167|m|ft|0}}, in [[Toubkal National Park]]]] There are 11 [[national parks]] in [[Morocco]]. [[Toubkal National Park]], established in 1942, is the oldest<ref name="HardyVorhees2005">{{cite book|last1=Hardy|first1=Paula|last2=Vorhees|first2=Mara|last3=Edsall|first3=Heidi|title=Morocco|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FKxWBLwMBqYC&pg=PA50|accessdate=31 January 2012|date=February 2005|publisher=Lonely Planet|isbn=978-1-74059-678-7|page=50}}</ref> and by far the most visited.<ref name="Humphrys2010">{{cite book|last=Humphrys|first=Darren|title=Frommer's Morocco|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OfcnGQxF42wC&pg=PA91|accessdate=31 January 2012|date=22 March 2010|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|isbn=978-0-470-56022-8|page=91}}</ref> The parks are situated rather well in-line,<ref>[http://fanack.com/uploads/pics/morocco_nature_map2_318px.jpg]{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> so it already allows [[Wildlife corridor|wildlife migration]] to some extent. The only missing component in this wildlife corridor is a gap between Al-Hoceima and Seghir (so roughly at the location of Hakkama). Closing this gap would facilitate wildlife passage (of mainly birds) to the Spanish park of [[Los Alcornocales]].
==National parks== * [[Al Hoceima National Park]] * [[Dakhla National Park]] (see [[Dakhla, Western Sahara|Dakhla]]) * [[Haut Atlas Oriental National Park]] * [[Ifrane National Park]] * [[Iriqui National Park]] * [[Khenifiss National Park]] * [[Khenifra National Park]] * [[Souss-Massa National Park]] * [[Talassemtane National Park]] * [[Tazekka National Park]] * [[Toubkal National Park]] * [[Merdja Zerka National Park]] (Permanent Biological Reserve)
==See also== *[[List of national parks]] * [[List of national parks in Africa]]
